            <p>All transcription factor overexpression data from tiling microarray experiments are available at NCBI GEO
                database under the accession number GSE59086 (<a
                        href="http://enews.patricbrc.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/tfoe-meta.xls"
                        >tfoe-meta.xls</a>)
                (Gene Expression Omnibus&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE59086"
                                                 >GSE59086</a>).
                Moreover, sample information for each experiment is available at MTB Network Portal (<a
                        href="http://networks.systemsbiology.net/mtb/content/TFOE-Searchable-Data-File"
                        >http://networks.systemsbiology.net/mtb/content/TFOE-Searchable-Data-File</a>).
                A searchable Excel file enabling easy query of this large dataset can also be downloaded from the
                portal.</p>
            <p>The same <a
                    href="/workspace/PATRIC@patricbrc.org/home/Special%20Collections/NIAID%20Systems%20Biology%20Centers/Omics4TB">TFOE
                dataset is also available from a public PATRIC workspace</a>, which allows users to view the gene
                expression data as an interactive and dynamic gene list and heat map.</p>

